# Git Workflow

- **One branch per feature.** Before starting a distinct feature/step, create a new
  branch off up-to-date `main`. Do all of that feature's commits on its branch.
  Naming: `feat/<slug>` (or `fix/<slug>`, `chore/<slug>`). For plan steps use
  `feat/stepN-<slug>` (e.g. `feat/step6-auth-jwt-rbac`).
- **Commit feature by feature.** After each self-contained feature/step passes its
  acceptance check, make one focused commit for it. Do not batch several unrelated
  features into a single commit.
- **Never push.** The user pushes and merges branches. Do not run `git push`
  (or `git push --force`) unless the user explicitly asks in that message.
- Use clear, conventional commit messages (e.g. `feat(backend): ...`, `fix(web): ...`,
  `chore: ...`) with a short body describing what changed and why when useful.
- Trunk is `main`, tracking `origin/main`; feature branches merge back into `main`.
